ommon owners act as a wage cartel, pushing labor prices below their competi=
tive level. Importantly, common owners transfer wealth from workers to shar=
eholders not by actively pursuing anticompetitive measures but rather by al=
locating more control to shareholders=E2=80=94control that can then be exer=
cised by other shareholders, such as hostile raiders and activist hedge fun=
